=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LFNoise1_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral mixed sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 52 Hz, featuring slow attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally rich.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: slow
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: rich
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 52.0631
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.1307
  harmonic_regularity: 0.8025
  pitch_clarity: 26.9771
  inharmonicity: 0.0389
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -31.5637
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LFNoise1 Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LFNoise1.html
// Tags: LFNoise1, Classes, noise, modulation
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ LFNoise1.ar(1000, 0.25) }.play;

// modulate frequency

{ LFNoise1.ar(XLine.kr(1000, 10000, 10), 0.25) }.play;

// as frequency modulator
(
{ SinOsc.ar(
        LFNoise1.ar(4, 400, 450),
        0, 0.2
    )
}.play;
)

// freq is the rate of starting points
{ var freq = 1000; [LFNoise1.ar(freq), Impulse.ar(freq)] }.plot
